055/**
056 * Really weird experimental noise meant to be like {@link ValueNoise}, but faster in higher dimensions by using the
057 * simplex grid that {@link SeededNoise} uses.
058 * <br>
059 * This gets its name from the playground toys (jacks) that are shaped like a 3-simplex (a tetrahedron).
060 */
061@Beta
062public class JackNoise implements Noise.Noise2D, Noise.Noise3D, Noise.Noise4D, Noise.Noise5D, Noise.Noise6D {

075    /**
076     * Computes the hash for a 3D int point and its dot product with a 3D double point as one step.
077     * @param seed
078     * @param x
079     * @param y
080     * @param z
081     * @param xd
082     * @param yd
083     * @param zd
084     * @return a double between -1.2571 and 1.2571, exclusive
085     */
086    protected static double gradCoord3D(long seed, int x, int y, int z, double xd, double yd, double zd) {
087        final int hash = HastyPointHash.hash32(x, y, z, seed) * 3;
088        return xd * grad3d[hash] + yd * grad3d[hash + 1] + zd * grad3d[hash + 2];
089    }
090    protected static double gradCoord5D(long seed, int x, int y, int z, int w, int u, double xd, double yd, double zd, double wd, double ud) {
091        final int hash = HastyPointHash.hash256(x, y, z, w, u, seed) * 5;
092        return xd * grad5d[hash] + yd * grad5d[hash + 1] + zd * grad5d[hash + 2] + wd * grad5d[hash + 3] + ud * grad5d[hash + 4];
093    }

148    protected static final double F2 = (Math.sqrt(3.0) - 1.0) / 2.0,
149            G2 = (3.0 - Math.sqrt(3.0)) / (2.0 * 3.0),
150            F3 = (Math.sqrt(4.0) - 1.0) / 3.0,
151            G3 = (4.0 - Math.sqrt(4.0)) / (3.0 * 4.0),
152            F4 = (Math.sqrt(5.0) - 1.0) / 4.0,
153            G4 = (5.0 - Math.sqrt(5.0)) / (4.0 * 5.0),
154            LIMIT4 = 0.62,
155            F5 = (Math.sqrt(6.0) - 1.0) / 5.0,
156            G5 = (6.0 - Math.sqrt(6.0)) / (5.0 * 6.0),
157            LIMIT5 = 0.7,
158            F6 = (Math.sqrt(7.0) - 1.0) / 6.0,
159            G6 = (7.0 - Math.sqrt(7.0)) / (6.0 * 7.0),//F6 / (1.0 + 6.0 * F6),

163        final double s = (x + y) * F2;
164        final int i = fastFloor(x + s),
165                j = fastFloor(y + s);
166        final double t = (i + j) * G2,
167                X0 = i - t,
168                Y0 = j - t,
169                x0 = x - X0,
170                y0 = y - Y0;
171        int i1, j1;
172        if (x0 > y0) {
173            i1 = 1;
174            j1 = 0;
175        } else {
176            i1 = 0;
177            j1 = 1;
178        }
179        final double
180                x1 = x0 - i1 + G2,
181                y1 = y0 - j1 + G2,
182                x2 = x0 - 1 + 2 * G2,
183                y2 = y0 - 1 + 2 * G2;
184        double n = 0.0;
185        // Calculate the contribution from the three corners for 2D gradient
186        double t0 = 0.75 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0;
187        if (t0 > 0) {
188            t0 *= t0;
189            n += t0 * t0 * (hashAll(i, j, seed) >> 10);
190        }
191        double t1 = 0.75 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1;
192        if (t1 > 0) {
193            t1 *= t1;
194            n += t1 * t1 * (hashAll(i + i1, j + j1, seed) >> 10);
195        }
196        double t2 = 0.75 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2;
197        if (t2 > 0)  {
198            t2 *= t2;
199            n += t2 * t2 * (hashAll(i + 1, j + 1, seed) >> 10);
200        }
201        // Use sin_, which takes an argument in turns rather than radians, to wrap values
202        return NumberTools.sin_(n * 0x1p-53);

208//            n0 = 0;

230    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final long seed) {
231        double n = 0.0;
232        final double s = (x + y + z) * F3;
233        final int i = fastFloor(x + s),
234                j = fastFloor(y + s),
235                k = fastFloor(z + s);
236
237        final double t = (i + j + k) * G3;
238        final double X0 = i - t, Y0 = j - t, Z0 = k - t,
239                x0 = x - X0, y0 = y - Y0, z0 = z - Z0;
240
241        int i1, j1, k1;
242        int i2, j2, k2;
243
244        if (x0 >= y0) {
245            if (y0 >= z0) {
246                i1 = 1;
247                j1 = 0;
248                k1 = 0;
249                i2 = 1;
250                j2 = 1;
251                k2 = 0;
252            } else if (x0 >= z0) {
253                i1 = 1;
254                j1 = 0;
255                k1 = 0;
256                i2 = 1;
257                j2 = 0;
258                k2 = 1;
259            } else {
260                i1 = 0;
261                j1 = 0;
262                k1 = 1;
263                i2 = 1;
264                j2 = 0;
265                k2 = 1;
266            }
267        } else {
268            if (y0 < z0) {
269                i1 = 0;
270                j1 = 0;
271                k1 = 1;
272                i2 = 0;
273                j2 = 1;
274                k2 = 1;
275            } else if (x0 < z0) {
276                i1 = 0;
277                j1 = 1;
278                k1 = 0;
279                i2 = 0;
280                j2 = 1;
281                k2 = 1;
282            } else {
283                i1 = 0;
284                j1 = 1;
285                k1 = 0;
286                i2 = 1;
287                j2 = 1;
288                k2 = 0;
289            }
290        }
291
292        double x1 = x0 - i1 + G3; // Offsets for second corner in (x,y,z) coords
293        double y1 = y0 - j1 + G3;
294        double z1 = z0 - k1 + G3;
295        double x2 = x0 - i2 + F3; // Offsets for third corner in (x,y,z) coords
296        double y2 = y0 - j2 + F3;
297        double z2 = z0 - k2 + F3;
298        double x3 = x0 - 0.5; // Offsets for last corner in (x,y,z) coords
299        double y3 = y0 - 0.5;
300        double z3 = z0 - 0.5;
301
302        // Calculate the contribution from the four corners
303        double t0 = 0.75 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0 - z0 * z0;
304        if (t0 > 0) {
305            t0 *= t0;
306            n += t0 * t0 * (hashAll(i, j, k, seed) >> 10);
307        }
308        double t1 = 0.75 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1 - z1 * z1;
309        if (t1 > 0) {
310            t1 *= t1;
311            n += t1 * t1 * (hashAll(i + i1, j + j1, k + k1, seed) >> 10);
312        }
313        double t2 = 0.75 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2 - z2 * z2;
314        if (t2 > 0) {
315            t2 *= t2;
316            n += t2 * t2 * (hashAll(i + i2, j + j2, k + k2, seed) >> 10);
317        }
318        double t3 = 0.75 - x3 * x3 - y3 * y3 - z3 * z3;
319        if (t3 > 0) {
320            t3 *= t3;
321            n += t3 * t3 * (hashAll(i + 1, j + 1, k + 1, seed) >> 10);
322        }
323        // Use sin_, which takes an argument in turns rather than radians, to wrap values
324        return NumberTools.sin_(n * 0x1.1p-53); 
325    }

327    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final double w, final long seed) {
328        double n = 0.0;
329        final double s = (x + y + z + w) * F4;
330        final int i = fastFloor(x + s), j = fastFloor(y + s), k = fastFloor(z + s), l = fastFloor(w + s);
331        final double[] gradient4DLUT = grad4d;
332        final double t = (i + j + k + l) * G4,
333                X0 = i - t,
334                Y0 = j - t,
335                Z0 = k - t,
336                W0 = l - t,
337                x0 = x - X0,
338                y0 = y - Y0,
339                z0 = z - Z0,
340                w0 = w - W0;
341        final int c = (x0 > y0 ? 128 : 0) | (x0 > z0 ? 64 : 0) | (y0 > z0 ? 32 : 0) | (x0 > w0 ? 16 : 0) | (y0 > w0 ? 8 : 0) | (z0 > w0 ? 4 : 0);
342        final int i1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] >>> 2,
343                j1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] >>> 2,
344                k1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] >>> 2,
345                l1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] >>> 2,
346                i2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] >>> 1 & 1,
347                j2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] >>> 1 & 1,
348                k2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] >>> 1 & 1,
349                l2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] >>> 1 & 1,
350                i3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] & 1,
351                j3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] & 1,
352                k3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] & 1,
353                l3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] & 1;
354        final double x1 = x0 - i1 + G4,
355                y1 = y0 - j1 + G4,
356                z1 = z0 - k1 + G4,
357                w1 = w0 - l1 + G4,
358                x2 = x0 - i2 + 2 * G4,
359                y2 = y0 - j2 + 2 * G4,
360                z2 = z0 - k2 + 2 * G4,
361                w2 = w0 - l2 + 2 * G4,
362                x3 = x0 - i3 + 3 * G4,
363                y3 = y0 - j3 + 3 * G4,
364                z3 = z0 - k3 + 3 * G4,
365                w3 = w0 - l3 + 3 * G4,
366                x4 = x0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
367                y4 = y0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
368                z4 = z0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
369                w4 = w0 - 1 + 4 * G4;
370        final int h0 = (hash256(i, j, k, l, seed) & 0xFC),
371                h1 = (hash256(i + i1, j + j1, k + k1, l + l1, seed) & 0xFC),
372                h2 = (hash256(i + i2, j + j2, k + k2, l + l2, seed) & 0xFC),
373                h3 = (hash256(i + i3, j + j3, k + k3, l + l3, seed) & 0xFC),
374                h4 = (hash256(i + 1, j + 1, k + 1, l + 1, seed) & 0xFC);
375        double t0 = LIMIT4 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0 - z0 * z0 - w0 * w0;
376        if(t0 > 0) {
377            t0 *= t0;
378            n += t0 * t0 * (x0 * gradient4DLUT[h0] + y0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 1] + z0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 2] + w0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 3]);
379        }
380        double t1 = LIMIT4 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1 - z1 * z1 - w1 * w1;
381        if (t1 > 0) {
382            t1 *= t1;
383            n += t1 * t1 * (x1 * gradient4DLUT[h1] + y1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 1] + z1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 2] + w1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 3]);
384        }
385        double t2 = LIMIT4 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2 - z2 * z2 - w2 * w2;
386        if (t2 > 0) {
387            t2 *= t2;
388            n += t2 * t2 * (x2 * gradient4DLUT[h2] + y2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 1] + z2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 2] + w2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 3]);
389        }
390        double t3 = LIMIT4 - x3 * x3 - y3 * y3 - z3 * z3 - w3 * w3;
391        if (t3 > 0) {
392            t3 *= t3;
393            n += t3 * t3 * (x3 * gradient4DLUT[h3] + y3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 1] + z3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 2] + w3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 3]);
394        }
395        double t4 = LIMIT4 - x4 * x4 - y4 * y4 - z4 * z4 - w4 * w4;
396        if (t4 > 0) {
397            t4 *= t4;
398            n += t4 * t4 * (x4 * gradient4DLUT[h4] + y4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 1] + z4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 2] + w4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 3]);
399        }
400        //return NumberTools.bounce(5.0 + 41.0 * n);
401        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 14.75 * n));
402    }

404    /**
405     * Thanks to Mark A. Ropper for
406     * <a href="https://computergraphics.stackexchange.com/questions/6408/what-might-be-causing-these-artifacts-in-5d-6d-simplex-noise">this implementation</a>.
407     * @param x x coordinate
408     * @param y y coordinate
409     * @param z z coordinate
410     * @param w w coordinate (4th dimension)
411     * @param u u coordinate (5th dimension)
412     * @param seed long value that should completely change the noise if it changes even slightly
413     * @return a continuous noise value between -1.0 and 1.0, both inclusive
414     */
415    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final double w, final double u, final long seed) {
416        double n0, n1, n2, n3, n4, n5;
417        double t = (x + y + z + w + u) * F5;
418        int i = fastFloor(x + t);
419        int j = fastFloor(y + t);
420        int k = fastFloor(z + t);
421        int l = fastFloor(w + t);
422        int h = fastFloor(u + t);
423        t = (i + j + k + l + h) * G5;
424        double X0 = i - t;
425        double Y0 = j - t;
426        double Z0 = k - t;
427        double W0 = l - t;
428        double U0 = h - t;
429        double x0 = x - X0;
430        double y0 = y - Y0;
431        double z0 = z - Z0;
432        double w0 = w - W0;
433        double u0 = u - U0;
434
435        int rankx = 0;
436        int ranky = 0;
437        int rankz = 0;
438        int rankw = 0;
439        int ranku = 0;
440
441        if (x0 > y0) rankx++; else ranky++;
442        if (x0 > z0) rankx++; else rankz++;
443        if (x0 > w0) rankx++; else rankw++;
444        if (x0 > u0) rankx++; else ranku++;
445
446        if (y0 > z0) ranky++; else rankz++;
447        if (y0 > w0) ranky++; else rankw++;
448        if (y0 > u0) ranky++; else ranku++;
449
450        if (z0 > w0) rankz++; else rankw++;
451        if (z0 > u0) rankz++; else ranku++;
452
453        if (w0 > u0) rankw++; else ranku++;
454
455        int i1 = 3 - rankx >>> 31;
456        int j1 = 3 - ranky >>> 31;
457        int k1 = 3 - rankz >>> 31;
458        int l1 = 3 - rankw >>> 31;
459        int h1 = 3 - ranku >>> 31;
460
461        int i2 = 2 - rankx >>> 31;
462        int j2 = 2 - ranky >>> 31;
463        int k2 = 2 - rankz >>> 31;
464        int l2 = 2 - rankw >>> 31;
465        int h2 = 2 - ranku >>> 31;
466
467        int i3 = 1 - rankx >>> 31;
468        int j3 = 1 - ranky >>> 31;
469        int k3 = 1 - rankz >>> 31;
470        int l3 = 1 - rankw >>> 31;
471        int h3 = 1 - ranku >>> 31;
472
473        int i4 = -rankx >>> 31;
474        int j4 = -ranky >>> 31;
475        int k4 = -rankz >>> 31;
476        int l4 = -rankw >>> 31;
477        int h4 = -ranku >>> 31;
478
479        double x1 = x0 - i1 + G5;
480        double y1 = y0 - j1 + G5;
481        double z1 = z0 - k1 + G5;
482        double w1 = w0 - l1 + G5;
483        double u1 = u0 - h1 + G5;
484
485        double x2 = x0 - i2 + 2 * G5;
486        double y2 = y0 - j2 + 2 * G5;
487        double z2 = z0 - k2 + 2 * G5;
488        double w2 = w0 - l2 + 2 * G5;
489        double u2 = u0 - h2 + 2 * G5;
490
491        double x3 = x0 - i3 + 3 * G5;
492        double y3 = y0 - j3 + 3 * G5;
493        double z3 = z0 - k3 + 3 * G5;
494        double w3 = w0 - l3 + 3 * G5;
495        double u3 = u0 - h3 + 3 * G5;
496
497        double x4 = x0 - i4 + 4 * G5;
498        double y4 = y0 - j4 + 4 * G5;
499        double z4 = z0 - k4 + 4 * G5;
500        double w4 = w0 - l4 + 4 * G5;

573    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z,
574                               final double w, final double u, final double v, final long seed) {
575        final double s = (x + y + z + w + u + v) * F6;
576
577        final int skewX = fastFloor(x + s), skewY = fastFloor(y + s), skewZ = fastFloor(z + s),
578                skewW = fastFloor(w + s), skewU = fastFloor(u + s), skewV = fastFloor(v + s);
579        final double[] m = mShared, cellDist = cellDistShared, gradient6DLUT = JackNoise.grad6d;
580        final int[] distOrder = distOrderShared,
581                intLoc = intLocShared;
582        intLoc[0] = skewX;
583        intLoc[1] = skewY;
584        intLoc[2] = skewZ;
585        intLoc[3] = skewW;
586        intLoc[4] = skewU;
587        intLoc[5] = skewV;
588
589        final double unskew = (skewX + skewY + skewZ + skewW + skewU + skewV) * G6;
590        cellDist[0] = x - skewX + unskew;
591        cellDist[1] = y - skewY + unskew;
592        cellDist[2] = z - skewZ + unskew;
593        cellDist[3] = w - skewW + unskew;
594        cellDist[4] = u - skewU + unskew;
595        cellDist[5] = v - skewV + unskew;
596
597        int o0 = (cellDist[0]<cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
598        int o1 = (cellDist[1]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
599        int o2 = (cellDist[2]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<=cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
600        int o3 = (cellDist[3]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<=cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<=cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
601        int o4 = (cellDist[4]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[4]<=cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[4]<=cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[4]<=cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[4]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
602        int o5 = 15-(o0+o1+o2+o3+o4);
603
604        distOrder[o0]=0;
605        distOrder[o1]=1;
606        distOrder[o2]=2;
607        distOrder[o3]=3;
608        distOrder[o4]=4;
609        distOrder[o5]=5;
610
611        double n = 0;
612        double skewOffset = 0;
613
614        for (int c = -1; c < 6; c++) {
615            if (c != -1) intLoc[distOrder[c]]++;
616
617            m[0] = cellDist[0] - (intLoc[0] - skewX) + skewOffset;
618            m[1] = cellDist[1] - (intLoc[1] - skewY) + skewOffset;
619            m[2] = cellDist[2] - (intLoc[2] - skewZ) + skewOffset;
620            m[3] = cellDist[3] - (intLoc[3] - skewW) + skewOffset;
621            m[4] = cellDist[4] - (intLoc[4] - skewU) + skewOffset;
622            m[5] = cellDist[5] - (intLoc[5] - skewV) + skewOffset;
623
624            double tc = LIMIT6;
625
626            for (int d = 0; d < 6; d++) {
627                tc -= m[d] * m[d];
628            }
629
630            if (tc > 0) {
631                final int h = hash256(intLoc[0], intLoc[1], intLoc[2], intLoc[3],
632                        intLoc[4], intLoc[5], seed) * 6;
633                final double gr = gradient6DLUT[h] * m[0] + gradient6DLUT[h + 1] * m[1]
634                        + gradient6DLUT[h + 2] * m[2] + gradient6DLUT[h + 3] * m[3]
635                        + gradient6DLUT[h + 4] * m[4] + gradient6DLUT[h + 5] * m[5];
636                tc *= tc;
637                n += gr * tc * tc;
638            }
639            skewOffset += G6;
640        }
641        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 7.5f * n));
642    }
